'''Hollyhill Hummingbird Farm''', a 501(c)(3) Nonprofit corporation, is an educational farm located in [[Santa Rosa, California]].<ref>Kurhi, Eric [http://www.mercurynews.com/bay-area-news/ci_22261054/cupertino-hills-farm-offers-lessons-and-break-from “Cupertino hills farm offers lessons and a break from Silicon Valley life”] San Jose Mercury News, December 28, 2012</ref> Its focus is on biodynamics, sustainability, and the ethical treatment of life.<ref>Hanson, Brittany [http://www.ocregister.com/articles/west-510709-farm-aerospace.html “From the air to the Earth”] OC Register, May 30, 2013</ref>
The Farm was founded in 2011, by Dave West, an aerospace engineer.<ref>UC Irvine Magazine, [http://communications.uci.edu/magazine/2013/spring/2013spring.pdf Spring 2013], p. 20</ref>  Hollyhill Hummingbird Farm's symbol of a [[hummingbird]] comes from the philosophy of [[symbiosis]].<ref>Wilson, Matt [http://www.mercurynews.com/cupertino/ci_23726213/not-too-many-things-work-hand-hand-like “Not too many things work hand in hand like Hummingbird Farm”] Cupertino Courier, July 24, 2013</ref>

The Farm grows fruit, vegetables, nuts, herbs, and grains with the help of community volunteers.<ref>[http://www.tvbusa.com/index.php?option=com_club&Itemid=142&type=gttp TVB(USA)] Jan 16 & 17, 2013 </ref>

