'''Iqrar Ahmad Khan''' is a [[Pakistani]] [[agricultural scientist]] and a professor of [[Horticulture]] at the [[University of Agriculture, Faisalabad]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.uaf.edu.pk/admin/vc_office.html | title = The Administration - Office of the Vice Chancellor | accessdate = 2011-01-11 | publisher = [[University of Agriculture, Faisalabad]]}}</ref> He served as a Vice Chancellor for University of Agriculture, Faisalabad from 2008 to 2017. He earned his Ph.D. from the [[University of California, Riverside]]. Khan has released a potato variety (PARS-70), pioneered the research on breeding seedless Kinnow and discovered two new botanical varieties of wheat.{{citation needed|date=March 2016}} He was author of STED funded Citrus Nursery Project launched at UAF.<ref>http://www.interface.edu.pk/students/Feb-08/Islamia-College-University-of-Wah.asp</ref>  He was instrumental in developing international/regional mango research program to combat the sudden death of mango.{{citation needed|date=March 2016}}
He was disqualified by Lahore high court on Wednesday 9 August 2017 discreet  (UAF) University of Agriculture, Faisalabad acting Vice-Chancellor Prof. Iqrar Ahmad Khan from his job and ordered  Prof Dr Zafar Iqbal its Pro-Vice Chancellor to look after the university's matters.<ref>https://www.dawn.com/news/1350708</ref>

