{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2011}} {{Use Australian English|date=September 2011}} {{Infobox project | name = Labshare consortium | logo = | website = {{URL|http://www.labshare.edu.au/project}} | commercial = No | type = [[Engineering]] [[education]] | location = [[Australia]] | owner = [[Australian Government]] | founder = Prof David Lowe | mission_statement = To create a nationally shared network of remote laboratories that will result in higher quality labs | established = Summer 2009 | funding = $3.8m provided between the period of 2009-2011 }}
'''Labshare consortium''' is a [[laboratory]] sharing initiative<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.labshare.edu.au/images/site/9.%20International_collaboration_in_remote_engineering_laboratories.pdf|title=International Collaboration in Remote Engineering Laboratories: an Approach to Development|author=A. Nafalski, Z. Nedic, J. Machotka, Ö. Göl, A. Scarino, J. Crichton, I. Gustavsson, J. M. Ferreira, D. Lowe, and S. Murray IEEE Transactions on Learning Technologies, 2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.labshare.edu.au/images/site/LabShare_Org_Models_Discussion_Paper.pdf|title=Organisation Models Discussion Paper Stage 1 : Key Issues and Requirements|publisher=Labshare}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.labshare.edu.au/images/site/1.%20Factors_that_impact_learning_outcomes_in_remote_laboratories.pdf|title=Factors that impact learning outcomes in Remote Laboratories|author1=C. Bright |author2=E. Lindsay |author3=D. Lowe |author4=S. Murray |author5=D. Liu |publisher=Ed-Media 2008|work=World Conference on Educational Multimedia, Hypermedia and Telecommunications, J. Luca and E. R. Weippl, Eds|location=Vienna, Austria}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.labshare.edu.au/images/site/2.%20Remote_laboratories_in_engineering_education_Trends_in_students_perceptions.pdf|title=Remote laboratories in Engineering Education: Trends in Students' Perceptions|author1=E. Lindsay |author2=D. Liu |author3=S. Murray |author4=D. Lowe |publisher=AaeE 2007|work=Eighteenth Annual Conference of the Australasian Association for Engineering Education, H. Søndergaard and R. Hadgraft, Eds.|location=Melbourne, Australia: Department of Computer Science and Software Engineering, The University of Melbourne, Melbourne Vic. 3010, Australia., 2007, p. (electronic publication).}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.labshare.edu.au/images/site/3.%20Establishment_reality_vs_maintenance_reality-How_real_is_real_enough.pdf|title=Establishment reality vs maintenance reality: how real is real enough?|author1=E. Lindsay |author2=S. Murray |author3=D. Liu |author4=D. Lowe |author5=C. Bright |publisher=SEFI 2008|work=36th Annual Conference of the European Society for Engineering Education Aalborg, Denmark: European Society for Engineering Education|year=2008}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.labshare.edu.au/images/site/5.%20Adapting_a_remote_laboratory_architecture_to_support_collaboration_and_supervision.pdf|title=Adapting a Remote Laboratory Architecture to Support Collaboration and Supervision|author1=D. Lowe |author2=C. Berry |author3=S. Murray |author4=E. Lindsay |publisher=REV 2009: 6th International Conference on Remote Engineering and Virtual Instrumentation, M. Auer, N. Gupta, and J. Pallis, Eds.|location=Bridgeport, USA: International Association of Online Engineering|year=2009|pages=103–108}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.labshare.edu.au/images/site/6.%20Evolving_remote_laboratory_architectures_to_leverage_emerging_internet_technologies.pdf|title=Evolving Remote Laboratory Architectures to Leverage Emerging Internet Technologies|author1=D. Lowe |author2=S. Murray |author3=E. Lindsay |author4=D. Liu |publisher=IEEE Transactions on Learning Technologies|year=2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.labshare.edu.au/images/site/7.%20Reflecting%20professional%20reality%20in%20remote%20laboratory%20experiences.pdf|title=Reflecting Professional Reality in Remote Laboratory Experiences|author1=D. Lowe |author2=S. Murray |author3=E. Lindsay |author4=D. Liu |author5=C. Bright |publisher=REV 2008|work=Remote Engineering and Virtual Instrumentation, M. E. Auer and R. Langmann, Eds.|location=Düsseldorf, Germany: International Association of Online Engineering|year=2008}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.labshare.edu.au/images/site/8.%20Experiences_with_a_hybrid_architecture_for_remote_laboratories.pdf|title=Experiences with a Hybrid Architecture for Remote Laboratories|author1=S. Murray |author2=D. Lowe |author3=E. Lindsay |author4=V. Lasky |author5=D. Liu |publisher=FiE 2008|work=The 38th Annual Frontiers in Education Conference|location=Saratoga Springs, USA|year=2008}}</ref> established by the Federal [[Commonwealth of Australia]] Government's [[Department of Education, Employment and Workplace Relations]] by their Diversity and Structural Adjustment Fund<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deewr.gov.au/dsa|title=Diversity and Structural Adjustment Fund|publisher=Government of Australia}}</ref> awarded the five [[Australian Technology Network]] Universities: [[University of South Australia]], [[Royal Melbourne Institute of Technology]], [[University of Technology Sydney]], [[Curtin University of Technology]] and [[Queensland University of Technology]], which supported the national sharing of remote labs as a [[consortium]] of [[Australian Technology Network]] Universities who would share remote laboratories.<ref>Callaghan, Harkin, Maguire (2007). "Paradigms in Remote Experimentation", ''International Journal of Online Engineering (iJOE)'', Vol 3, No 4 (2007)[http://online-journals.org/i-joe/article/view/468]</ref>
The University of South Australia was first to establish its '''NetLab''' remote lab in 2008.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.unisanet.unisa.edu.au/staff/homepage.asp?Name=Andrew.Nafalski|title=Professor Andrew Nafalski Home Page|publisher=[[University of South Australia]]|date=27 August 2010}}</ref>
