'''''The Universe for Beginners''''', republished as '''''Introducing the Universe''''', is a 1993 [[graphic novel|graphic]] [[study guide]] to [[cosmology]] written by [[Felix Pirani]] and illustrated by [[Christine Roche]]. The volume, according to the publisher's website, "recounts the revolutions in [[physics]] and [[astronomy]]," from "[[Aristotle]] to [[Isaac Newton|Newton]]," and, "[[Einstein]] to [[Quantum Mechanics]]," "that underlie the present-day picture of the universe."<ref name="IB01">{{cite web |title=Introducing the Universe: A Graphic Guide |first= |last= |url=http://www.iconbooks.com/blog/title/introducing-the-universe/ |work=Icon Books |date= |accessdate=2017-01-22 }}</ref>

==Publication History==
This volume was originally published in the UK by Icon Books in 1993 as ''The Universe for Beginners'', and subsequently republished with different covers as ''Introducing the Universe'' and ''Introducing the Universe: A Graphic Guide''.

